"Kruse H.","Refrigerant use in Europe",2000,"ASHRAE Journal","42","9",,"16","18+21",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0034260322&partnerID=40&md5=f1e65bb3e5d8e7af81d4cc26ff4f0e61","Res. Ctr. for Refrigeration Technol., Hannover, Germany","Kruse, H., Res. Ctr. for Refrigeration Technol., Hannover, Germany","There are two ways to fulfill the requirements of the Kyoto Protocol concerning greenhouse gas emissions. One way is to tighten the refrigerant systems to reduce leakage of hydrofluorocarbon (HFC) refrigerants, and the other by using fluids with very low Global Warming Potential (GWF). To further improve such a system, CO2 is used as a secondary coolant to reduce high energy consumption.",,"Air conditioning; Azeotropes; Chlorofluorocarbons; Developing countries; Global warming; Greenhouse effect; Hydrogen inorganic compounds; Laws and legislation; Propane; Global Warming Potential; Greenhouse gases; Hydrocarbon propane; Hydrofluorocarbon; Ozone depleting potential; Refrigerants",,,,,,"Montreal Protocol 1991 Assessment, Report of the Refrigeration, Air Conditioning and Heat Pumps Technical Options Committee, , UNEP, December; (1991) DOE/AFEAS GW Project: Energy and Global Warming Impacts of CFC Alternative Technologies, , Executive Summary, Oak Ridge National Laboratory, December; Arnemann, M., Gebhardt, D., Kruse, H., Experimentelle bewertung neuer Kältemittelgemische als Ersatz für R-22 und R502 (1995) DIE KÄLTE und Klimatechnik, 2, p. 66; (1997) DOE/AFEAS TEWI-III Report: Energy and Global Warming Impacts of HFC Refrigerants and Emerging Technologies, , TEWI Phase 3, Oak Ridge National Laboratory, March; Kruse, H., Enkemann, T., Minderung des Energieverbrauchs indirekter Systeme durch Auswahl von Kälteträgern (1997) Ki Luftund Kältetechnik, 10, p. 472; Enkemann, T., Kälteträger für Anlagen mit indirekter Kühlung, Übersicht, FKW-Seminar XVIII: Aktuelle Entwicklungen in der Kältetechnik in Supermärkten/Gewerbekälte (1996), Hannover, December(1